quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  30,1,ELIF. LAM. MIM
  30,2,THE GREEKS have been defeated
  30,3,"In a land hard by: But after their defeat they shall defeat their foes"
  30,4,In a few years. First and last is the affair with God. And on that day shall the faithful rejoice
  30,5,"In the aid of their God: He aideth whom He will; and He is the Mighty, the Merciful"
  30,6,"It is the promise of God: To his promise God will not be untrue: but most men know it not"
  30,7,"They know the outward shews of this life present, but of the next life are they careless"
  30,8,"Have they not considered within themselves that God hath not created the Heavens and the Earth and all that is between them but for a serious end, and for a fixed term? But truly most men believe not that they shall meet their Lord"
  30,9,"Have they never journeyed through the land, and seen what hath been the end of those who were before them? Mightier were they than these in strength; and they broke up the land, and dwelt in it in greater numbers than they who dwell there now; and their apostles came to them with proofs of their mission: and it was not God who would wrong them, but they wronged themselves"
  30,10,"Then evil was the end of the evil doers; because they had treated our signs as lies, and laughed them to scorn"